    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "As I said in the other issue, numpy has the same behaviour as pandas (which is strange), although there docs say the same as we think it should be: \"Boolean arrays must be of the same shape as the initial dimensions of the array being indexed\" (http://docs.scipy.org/doc/numpy/user/basics.indexing.html#boolean-or-mask-index-arrays):\n\n```\nIn [2]: np.__version__\nOut[2]: '1.8.1'\n\nIn [3]: a = np.arange(5)\n\nIn [4]: a\nOut[4]: array([0, 1, 2, 3, 4])\n\nIn [5]: a[np.array([True, False, True])]\nOut[5]: array([0, 2])\n```\n"
  },
